            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>733</offset>
                <text>Maternal body height was 164 cm and paternal height was 187 cm.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>797</offset>
                <text>Midparental height was estimated as 169 cm (+1 SD score).</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>855</offset>
                <text>No noticeably short individual was reported in the family.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>914</offset>
                <text>The patient started forming syllables and walked approximately at one year of age.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>997</offset>
                <text>Laboratory analyses showed normal complete blood cell counts with normally functioning kidneys and liver.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>1103</offset>
                <text>The patient was euthyroid and serological analyses for gluten-sensitive enteropathy were negative.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>1202</offset>
                <text>Her bone age was in line with her chronological age.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>1255</offset>
                <text>Her karyotype was 46,XX and bone X-rays revealed a lumbar lordosis (Figure 1).</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>1334</offset>
                <text>Echocardiographic findings were normal.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>1374</offset>
                <text>Serum insulin-like growth factor 1 (IGF-1) level was 47 ng/mL (&lt;-2 SD score) and serum IGF binding protein-3 (IGFBP-3) level was 2800 mg/mL (between +1/+2 SD score).</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>1540</offset>
                <text>L-dopa stimulation test scores revealed a peak GH response of 3.7 ng/mL.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>1618</offset>
                <text>Our patient had prenatal growth retardation and a significantly short stature in addition to triangular face, a long philtrum, a fleshy nose tip, prominent mouth and lips with pointed chin (Figure 2), as well as lumbar lordosis which collectively suggested a syndromic short stature.</text>
